r’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Henry de Longchamp was born in 1210, in Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Henry de Longchamp, was 22 and his mother, Rohesia de Lacy, was 50. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan of Wilton. He died in 1264, in Wilton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1210–1264":"1210–1264","1213–1253":"1213–1253","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1240–1302":"1240–1302","1253–1330":"1253–1330","1188–Male":"1188–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1302":"1302","1213":"1213","1210":"1210","1188":"1188","1253":"1253","1264":"1264","1330":"1330","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","about 1253":"umbes 1253","1160":"1160","about 1240":"umbes 1240","Wilton, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, England","Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglaterra, United Kingdom":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1210–1264":"1210–1264","1213–1253":"1213–1253","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1240–1302":"1240–1302","1253–1330":"1253–1330","1188–Male":"1188–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1302":"1302","1213":"1213","1210":"1210","1188":"1188","1253":"1253","1264":"1264","1330":"1330","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","about 1253":"noin 1253","1160":"1160","about 1240":"noin 1240","Wilton, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, England","Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdist